<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The locking/trace/unlock macros are no-ops in this project configuration, producing executed operations that have no effect. LFS_LOCK(cfg) is defined to '((void)cfg,0)', so err is always 0 and the branch 'if (err) { return err; }' can never be taken (the error-return path is redundant). LFS_TRACE expands to nothing, and LFS_UNLOCK(cfg) expands to '((void)cfg)' (just a value-evaluation), so the unlock/trace calls do not affect behaviour. These executed operations can be removed without changing program behaviour, which constitutes dead code under Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
